=============================
Defining a Permutation Matrix                                            [TOC]
=============================

In this example we show how you can define your own general matrix type and
support the matrix-vector product and matrix-matrix product for it.  The matrix
type we define represents a _permutation_.

Our Permutation Matrix
======================
The permutation is derived from `GeneralMatrix` and we define functions
`blas::mv` and `blas::mm` for it.
  :import: flens/examples/permutation.h

Example
=======
That's it.  Now we just use it.
  :import: flens/examples/permutation.cc

